                        ✔ Students should also have a working dev mode, check that webpack dev server is set up and that they have an npm script that starts the server @done(21-08-17 04:43)
                        
    ✔ Content @done(21-08-17 04:44)

                        ✔ Only one html file is required, but it must be at src/views/ or src/html. Must contain valid semantic html @done(21-08-17 04:43)

                        ✔ There will be a minimum of 2 javascript files in the src/js folder. All files in the js folder must be found by webpack. @done(21-08-17 04:43)

                        ✔ There must be a styles or scss folder. The project provides a base file, but the header, footer, form, and main files should be added to by the student, similar to the course. @done(21-08-17 04:44)
                        
Functionality


    ✔ API @done(21-08-17 04:45)

                    ✔ The app should make a successful call to the api on form submission. @done(21-08-17 04:44)
                    ✔ If this is successful, the api keys and response handling were done correctly. @done(21-08-17 04:45)
                    ✔ You can check that the api keys are found in server.js or a similar node file. It is not acceptable for an api key to be set in a client facing file (like index.js) @done(21-08-17 04:44)

                    ✔ Information from the api response must show up in the view. It is not enough for the response to be logged to the console or saved in js, etc.. @done(21-08-17 04:45)

    ✔ Offline Functionality @done(21-08-17 04:46)

                    ✔ The project must have set up service workers in webpack. @done(21-08-17 04:45)

    ✔ Testing @done(21-08-17 04:46)

                    ✔ Check that the project has Jest installed, that there is an npm script to run Jest, and that the tests all pass. Every src/js file should have at least one test. @done(21-08-17 04:45)

    ✔ Interactions @done(21-08-17 04:46)

                    ✔ The page built can be very simple, but should include: @done(21-08-17 04:46)

